                    <comment id="12422214" author="jukkaz" created="Wed, 19 Jul 2006 19:04:38 +0100"  >Fixed in revision 423547 by catching and logging all index filter exceptions (even unchecked ones). After considering this issue I don&amp;#39;t think it makes sense to give the index filters veto powers over saving content. They are not validators, so if a binary property cannot be parsed for text content because of a file format error or some similar problem, the indexer should return an empty reader instead of trying to revert the save or somehow signal the client application.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The requested functionality would be better implemented by extending the value constraint support in Jackrabbit. Please file a separate feature request if you still need this functionality.</comment>
